    <h3 data-renderer-start-pos="1" id="Glossary">Glossary<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-1i2mldy" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h3>
    <h5 data-renderer-start-pos="11" id="Permissible-tenant-values">Permissible tenant values<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-86thoz" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h5>
    <ul>
    <li><p><a href="http://swig.gy/" class="sc-gzOgki dwCPUL" title="http://swig.gy">swig.gy</a> → Non-prod cluster</p></li>
    <li><p>swiggy.cloud → Production cluster</p></li>
    </ul>
    <h5 data-renderer-start-pos="107" id="Permissible-environment-values-(non-exhaustive)">Permissible environment values (non-exhaustive)<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-86thoz" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h5>
    <ul>
    <li><p>d1</p></li>
    <li><p>u4</p></li>
    <li><p>sf</p></li>
    <li><p>staging</p></li>
    <li><p>preprod</p></li>
    <li><p>production</p></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="ak-editor-panel sc-gisBJw BKlvh" data-panel-type="info">
    <span class="ak-editor-panel__icon"><span class="css-1w1m1we" role="img" aria-label="Panel info"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span>
    <div class="ak-editor-panel__content">
    <p>Refer to the following document for debugging crashing RoCK instances<br />
    <span data-inline-card="true" data-card-url="https://swiggy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SHUT/pages/2369849541"><span class="loader-wrapper"><a href="https://swiggy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SHUT/pages/2369849541" class="sc-gGBfsJ hqDDVV">https://swiggy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SHUT/pages/2369849541</a></span></span></p>
    </div>
    </div>
    <h3 data-renderer-start-pos="288" id="Status-of-the-application">Status of the application<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-1i2mldy" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h3>
    <p>coast get status -e &lt;env-name&gt; -r singapore -s &lt;service-name&gt; -t &lt;tenant&gt;</p>
    <h5 data-renderer-start-pos="390" id="Example">Example<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-86thoz" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h5>
    <ul>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in production environment, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get status -e production -r singapore -s demo-rock -t swiggy.cloud</strong></p></li>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in sf environment, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get status -e sf -r singapore -s demo-rock -t swig.gy</strong></p></li>
    </ul>
    <h3 data-renderer-start-pos="706" id="Get-logs-for-the-application">Get logs for the application<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-1i2mldy" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h3>
    <p>coast get status -e &lt;env-name&gt; -r singapore -n &lt;service-name&gt; -t &lt;tenant&gt; -i &lt;instance-id&gt;</p>
    <p>You can get the instance id of the containers using the coast get status command mentioned above.</p>
    <h5 data-renderer-start-pos="928" id="Example.1">Example<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-86thoz" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h5>
    <ul>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in production environment and one of the instance id is <em>demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</em>, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get logs -e production -r singapore -n demo-rock -t swiggy.cloud -i demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</strong></p></li>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in sf environment and one of the instance id is <em>demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</em>, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get logs -e sf -r singapore -n demo-rock -t swig.gy -i demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</strong></p></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="ak-editor-panel sc-gisBJw BKlvh" data-panel-type="info">
    <span class="ak-editor-panel__icon"><span class="css-1w1m1we" role="img" aria-label="Panel info"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span>
    <div class="ak-editor-panel__content">
    <p>You can also see your application logs pushed in S3<br />
    <span data-inline-card="true" data-card-url="https://swiggy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ROCK/pages/1466043787/How+to+access+Rock+Logs+stored+in+s3+bucket"><span class="loader-wrapper"><span><a href="https://swiggy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ROCK/pages/1466043787/How+to+access+Rock+Logs+stored+in+s3+bucket" class="sc-gGBfsJ eDbmRC">https://swiggy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ROCK/pages/1466043787/How+to+access+Rock+Logs+stored+in+s3+bucket</a></span></span></span></p>
    </div>
    </div>
    <h3 data-renderer-start-pos="1472" id="Get-K8s-events-for-the-any-pod">Get K8s events for the any pod<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-1i2mldy" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h3>
    <p>coast get events -e &lt;env-name&gt; -r singapore -s &lt;service-name&gt; -t &lt;tenant&gt; -i &lt;instance-id&gt;</p>
    <p>You can get the instance id of the containers using the coast get status command mentioned above.</p>
    <p>Example:</p>
    <ul>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in production environment and one of the instance id is <em>demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</em>, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get events -e production -r singapore -s demo-rock -t swiggy.cloud -i demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</strong></p></li>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in sf environment and one of the instance id is <em>demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</em>, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get events -e sf -r singapore -s demo-rock -t swig.gy -i demo-rock-78cf6d59cb-mzx47</strong></p></li>
    </ul>
    <h3 data-renderer-start-pos="2187" id="Get-running-version-of-any-RoCK-application">Get running version of any RoCK application<span class="heading-anchor-wrapper" role="presentation"><span class="css-1i2mldy" role="img" aria-label="copy"><img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," /></span></span></h3>
    <p>coast get runningVersion -s &lt;service-name&gt;-e &lt;env-name&gt; -r &lt;env-location&gt; -t &lt;tenant&gt;</p>
    <p>Example:</p>
    <ul>
    <li><p>For a service name demo-rock deployed in production environment, the command should be<br />
    <strong>coast get runningVersion -s demo-rock -e production -r singapore -t swiggy.cloud</strong></p></li>
    </ul>
